'626\t' + _x("npc conversation", "One advantage of the sword and the dagger is that skilled users can wield a blade in their left hands instead of using a shield.  Even a fluff head like yourself should understand why that could help.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Combo weapons") + '\r\n'
'627\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I know how easy it is for us warriors to scoff at the weak mages out there, but they can make themselves useful at times.  Many of their spells can increase your fighting ability by making you faster, or hit better, or more resistant to damage.  As long as they can pull their own weight, mages make excellent travelling companions.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magic") + '\r\n'
'628\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Travelling spells represent the most important class of spells for all magic-using people.  Not only do they let you get to places you couldn't get to without  magic, but they let you visit things like health and magic-boosting fountains in remote areas, and use those abilities in dangerous dungeons and castles where you need them.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Travelling Spells") + '\r\n'
'629\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Agar's 'finest' creations, these floating heads have surprising intelligence and great power at their command.  Their gaze is enough to put you to sleep.  Rumors abound of even more powerful eyes that can cause panic or even complete insanity.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Flying Eyes") + '\r\n'
'630\t' + _x("npc conversation", "A few Guilds of the Self exist in the lands.  Combining knowledge of mind, spirit, and body, these guilds offer a more generalized study than any of the individual guilds can offer.  Their knowledge of the individual schools isn't nearly as complete, however.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Self Magic Guilds") + '\r\n'
'631\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Don't let the name fool you:  Abdul's Discount stores offer really great quality for low, low prices.  He also didn't pay me to say that on Thursdays.  Honest.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Abdul's Discounts") + '\r\n'
'632\t' + _x("npc conversation", "In the north, businesses are controlled by a few monopolies that prevent competition by any means necessary, even by extortion.  The Shadow Guild and the Thieves' Guild have already started to clash over rights in areas like Silver Cove and Free Haven.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Shadow Guild") + '\r\n'
'633\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Take my word for it when I say the Mire is a bad place to find yourself at night.  The Necromancer's Guild 'retired' to the swamp after Archibald's defeat in the Succession War, and evidence of their handiwork is walking around the swamp freely.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Mire of the Damned") + '\r\n'
'634\t' + _x("npc conversation", "You can avoid a lengthy jail sentence for any crimes you've been committing by receiving forgiveness at the temples.  If you run into a guard before receiving forgiveness for significant crimes, you could be looking at a year in jail, or even longer.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Jail Sentences") + '\r\n'
'635\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Many monsters won't reason with you, no matter how eloquently you phrase your requests.  You need to recognize hopelessly aggressive monsters and be rid of them as fast as possible.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Monsters") + '\r\n'
'636\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Many people don't really care for tinkers because we wander and do odd jobs that guilds would like to charge a lot for.  But you like me, don't you?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Undesirables") + '\r\n'
'637\t' + _x("npc conversation", "With all the troubles that have been going on, business has been great for me.  People have found the need to lock up their possessions to try and protect them from marauders or looters.  It's good to know I can give people at least a small sense of security in these dark times.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Danger") + '\r\n'
'638\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I bought a treasure map from this treasure map salesman I met awhile ago and it says the dread pirate captain Silveka buried his treasure under a tree on one of the  islands east of Free Haven.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Treasure Map") + '\r\n'
'639\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Loretta is my kind of person.  She makes her own luck, and it's almost always good.  She's got confidence, and that's something you can't just buy.  I'm sure that's the reason she's so successful: a confident, positive outlook.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Loretta Fleise") + '\r\n'
'640\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I'm sure you've seen the obelisks scattered around the Kingdom.  They say there's a riddle in them just waiting to be solved that shows where to find a great horde of buried treasure.  No one's ever done it, though.  At least, no one I've ever heard of.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Obelisks") + '\r\n'
'641\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Aye, I've worked in Osric's army before, tending camp and preparing food and cataloguing supplies.  He's a fair man, and an excellent leader.  He knows how to keep his troops motivated, let me tell you.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Osric Temper") + '\r\n'
'642\t' + _x("npc conversation", "There are only three certainties in life:  The first is death.  The second is taxes.  And the third is the fact that you'll hear that joke sooner or later.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Death and Taxes") + '\r\n'
'643\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Banks are a safe place to store money.  Unless you personally own a secure, guarded vault, your best bet is to put your money in a bank.  You don't collect interest on your money, but because the banks don't lend out money, you don't have to worry about losing it.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Banks") + '\r\n'
'644\t' + _x("npc conversation", "One of the few exports the Islands of Regna have going for them, besides piracy, is sugar, cocoa, and cinnamon.  If it weren't for those, I'd say we should ship the Temple of Baa over to Regna and let them sink all those islands!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Herbs from Regna") + '\r\n'
'645\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Different inns charge different amounts for the food they sell, but don't be fooled.  The more expensive food will generally last longer than the cheaper stuff.  It's important to have food that will last when you plan to be out for long periods of time.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Food Prices") + '\r\n'
'646\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I can't say I know much about travel over water, but from what I've heard, you can either take a ship to the islands, or Walk on Water to get there.  Ships all have complicated itineraries– be sure to ask the shipping company before you book passage when they do return voyages!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Island travel") + '\r\n'
'647\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It's a shame that Catherine was pulled away to her father's funeral so soon after Roland's death.  That poor woman has suffered too many tragedies too soon.  It's even sadder that she's leaving Nicolai here while she's gone.  He's too young to have to deal with all of this on top of the crises affecting the kingdom.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Catherine") + '\r\n'
'648\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Necromancer's Guild first appeared publicly during Archibald's brief reign 10 years ago.  They were around before that, but they kept themselves secret, knowing people wouldn't appreciate them.  When Roland became king, he outlawed the guild and ordered the leaders arrested.  None of them stayed around long enough for that, though, and now they're nowhere to be found.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Necromancers") + '\r\n'
'649\t' + _x("npc conversation", "There are many islands that can only be reached with a combination of boat travel and the Walk on Water spell.  Many of them are inhabited by the most horrible of monsters, but often the finest treasures can be found on them.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Islands") + '\r\n'
'650\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dragons are not only adept combatants, they are wily spell casters.  Few people appreciate the dragons' grasp of magic, and many cocky warriors find themselves unprepared for the dragons' true power.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dragons") + '\r\n'
'651\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Erathia is out of even Town Portal's long range.  That continent is a full six week's worth of sea travel away.  There are a lot of islands and sub-continents between here and there, all of them filled with petty kingdoms and tribes looking to rob travelers of their valuables, their freedom, or their lives.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Erathia") + '\r\n'
'652\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I've seen a few devils in my travels, and they are fierce to behold.  I've had to rescue a few people from devil attacks, and I  was amazed at their coordination and prowess in combat.  They must have excellent training to be that proficient.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Devils") + '\r\n'
'653\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I fear the Night of Shooting Stars was an omen of the worst kind.  It didn't take long for our good king to disappear after that night, and for the Temple of Baa to arrive, did it?  And all this talk about devils in the west…these are evil omens indeed!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Night of Shooting Stars") + '\r\n'
'654\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Once I was hired by a noble to entertain him and his wife on Star Lake, playing music while they picnicked in a boat. When we approached the south end of the island at the center of the lake, we saw the most hideous beast– a woman with snakes for hair– on the shore of the island.  She took one look at my noble benefactors and they turned to stone before my eyes.  It was all I could do to row away before I joined them.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Medusas") + '\r\n'
'655\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Flight spells provide a way to get past mountains and walls and other such obstacles.  There is a limit on how high you can fly with the Fly spell, though.  Some peaks rise too high to pass with magical flying.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Flight Spells") + '\r\n'
'656\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Hareck IX has got to be the best leader in the world.  Not only is he the only Emperor in the world, he's the only leader I've ever heard of that does common work like the rest of his people.  Like when there's taxes to be collected on shipping, Hareck's right there with the rest of us.  Boarding, fighting, cursing, drinking, whatever.  Hareck's a real down to earth kind of Emperor.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Hareck IX") + '\r\n'
'657\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Every squire knows that a weapon is of no use broken.  Every warrior should know how to repair his own equipment, or be at the whim of the smiths' schedules.  Knowing how to repair your weapon is part of mastering your weapon.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Repairing") + '\r\n'
'658\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Of all the malicious mischief makers in the world, Necromancers are by far the worst.  Their 'science' is very new, and they know just enough to get themselves and the rest of the world in trouble.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Ghosts") + '\r\n'
'659\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Resting revives your body and mind.  Camping gives you a chance to relax, talk, celebrate– to just unwind a little and rest off some of the stress and worry of the remainder of the day.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Resting") + '\r\n'
'660\t' + _x("npc conversation", "A wise negotiator once said, 'On whether 'tis better to be loved or to be feared, choose both.  But if a choice between the two must be made, choose fear.'– Words to live by, my friend.  Words to live by.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fear and Love") + '\r\n'
'661\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Up north, it's not uncommon for wealthy businessmen to preserve their position in the market by hiring thugs to trim their competition.  Trade wars can become quite literally wars.  It's best to not get involved in any merchant disputes.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Organized Crime") + '\r\n'
'662\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Some of the best perception and lock-picking teachers hang out in Thieves' Guilds.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Thieves' Guilds") + '\r\n'
'663\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Even if King Roland did something bad to cause heaven to abandon him, I don't suppose that his son Nicolai deserves it.  After all, he's only ten years old.  Maybe heaven will smile upon him and give him heaven's mandate to rule wisely.  That would be nice.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Nicolai Ironfist") + '\r\n'
'664\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I can't leave the towns and castles without some bandit taking away what little money I actually manage to save.  Why can't the guards do something about all the brigands?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Bandits") + '\r\n'
'665\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Indigo from Regna was cut off a decade ago when the king outlawed trade with that pirate kingdom.  I can understand why he did that, but I sure am tired of the indigo shortage.  I can't dye anything blue or purple!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Indigo") + '\r\n'
'666\t' + _x("npc conversation", "What do you want from me?  I'm just a worker; I'm not here to amuse you.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Entertainment") + '\r\n'
'667\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It sure has been raining a lot, lately.  It would be terrible if the clouds ran out of rain and the rivers ran dry because all the water had been used up during these storms.  If the rivers all ran dry, I'd be ruined!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Rivers") + '\r\n'
'668\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Chests and boxes aren't the only things that can hold treasure.  Barrels can also hold valuables, so don't forget to search them, too.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Barrels") + '\r\n'
'669\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Shipping has slowed from Erathia, which is where I get all the paints I need for my work.  That's the land the queen comes from.  I wonder if there's a problem over there?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Paints") + '\r\n'
'670\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I don't know who makes them, but every Baa priest has a cloak with the symbol of Baa on it.  I wish I had the job of making all those cloaks, I'd be rich!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Baa Cloaks") + '\r\n'
'671\t' + _x("npc conversation", "History is the sound of soft-soled slippers going down the stairs while hobnail boots climb up the stairs.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Hobnail Boots") + '\r\n'
'672\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I sure wish I could learn to do something other than dig ditches, but I'm just not bright enough.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Promotion") + '\r\n'
'673\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Flour's been going bad early this year, even though it's properly stored in sealed containers.  I wonder what's going on?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Flour") + '\r\n'
'674\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Don't forget that you can store things in cabinets.  Chests aren't the only places to keep your treasure.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Cabinets") + '\r\n'
'675\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The roads of Enroth are made of flagstones from the hills near Kriegspire.  They were placed long ago by the people who first settled Enroth, and those first roads have never eroded or decayed in any way.  Very odd.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Flagstones") + '\r\n'
'676\t' + _x("npc conversation", "What do you call a jittery sorceress?\n\nA twitch!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Joke of the Day") + '\r\n'
'677\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dark days are upon us, mark my words!  Never have I seen so many monsters and so little game.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dark Days") + '\r\n'
'678\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Nothing is worse than trying to beg near Silver Cove.  All the people there are so greedy!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Silver Cove") + '\r\n'
'679\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Shadow Guild is the best place to find a buyer willing to take stolen cattle.  There's nothing they won't do!  They're great, AND they charge less than the regular Thieves' Guild.  You gotta try them out!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Underworld") + '\r\n'
'680\t' + _x("npc conversation", "With the lack of animals and all the problems lately, I should probably just become a bounty hunter.  I could probably make a fortune tracking down all the lawbreakers.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Bounty Hunter") + '\r\n'
'681\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The most demanding master to have to work for is Osric Temper.  No one else shouts as much, or talks as quickly during a dictation.  I will say this though– of all the Lords, he is the only that seems to be on top of the devil situation we all know is so serious.  Unpleasant to work for to be sure, but he has the interests of the kingdom at heart.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dictation") + '\r\n'
'682\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Have you spoken with Baa today?  Let me help you come to grips with your problems and show you a better way; it will only take a little of your time.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Baa") + '\r\n'
'683\t' + _x("npc conversation", "A lot of people complain about taxes, but I just want to say I like them.  How could clerk's offices function without tax money?  How would people get permits and licenses without us?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Taxes") + '\r\n'
'684\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The towers outside the towns shoot at flying creatures that we'd normally have a difficult time handling.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dragon Towers") + '\r\n'
'685\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Most people don't have confidence in Nicolai.  I'll bet you 3 to 1 odds that he gets thrown out before his next birthday.  What'd ya say?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Ironfist Dynasty") + '\r\n'
'686\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I do hope that the queen returns from her trip to her homeland soon.  Even if she is a foreign queen she will supply some semblance of order to our besieged kingdom.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Queen Catherine") + '\r\n'
'687\t' + _x("npc conversation", "No one knows where the Supreme Temple of Baa is, but I've heard only full-fledged priests and high temple officials are allowed to visit.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Supreme Temple") + '\r\n'
'688\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Do goblins have names?  Or families?  Why are they evil?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Goblins") + '\r\n'
'689 F\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The best all around weapon shop in Enroth is the Knight's Paradise, run by Eric Regent.  You can't buy better weapons anywhere else in the kingdom. ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Knight's Paradise") + '\r\n'
'690\t' + _x("npc conversation", "You know, metal for arms and armor used to be a lot cheaper before Snergle wrested the dwarven throne away from Rocklin, the old King of the Dwarves.  Sure would be nice if someone fixed Snergle's wagon.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dwarves") + '\r\n'
'691\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Once you are a member of a particular type of magic guild, you won't need to keep buying membership into different branches of the same guild.  A member of the Guild of Fire, for instance, need not buy membership in another Fire Guild in order to take advantage of their services.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magic Guilds") + '\r\n'
'692\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Albert Newton is the Lord of Mist, and he is truly the patron of all who hold dear the mystical arts.  If you have a question about magic, Mist is where you should look for an answer.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Island of Mist") + '\r\n'
'693\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Beware travel in the swamps south of Castle Temper.  The undead are said to roam about freely, unafraid of the living or the sun.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Swamps") + '\r\n'
'694\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I never seen one, but I've heard stories of magical portals– doorways– that lead instantly from one part of Enroth to another.  That would take all the fun out of travelling, wouldn't it?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magic Portals") + '\r\n'
'695\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Aptly named, Dragonsand is full of both dragons and sand.  I think the most powerful dragons are more than a match for the devils, or the devils would have long ago taken over the desert.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dragonsand") + '\r\n'
'696\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It is said that one of the islands east of Free Haven hides the buried treasure of Silveka the pirate.  Now, I know these stories are a dime dozen, but I swear this one is true!  If only the map could be found…") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Buried Treasure") + '\r\n'
'697\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Isle of the Hermit is a fairly large volcanic isle in the southwest of Enroth. No one goes there and it's more barren than even the wastelands.  It was named when Lord Terrance made a joke about a hermit living there to get away from it all.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Isle of the Hermit") + '\r\n'
'698\t' + _x("npc conversation", "All of the Necromancers in the Kingdom have been banished, happily, except the ones who took their black art too far and became liches.     The worst of those liches, Archibald's former general Lord Corlagon, has taken up residence in the south eastern portion of the Mire of the Damned.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Necromancy") + '\r\n'
'699\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It IS possible to combine compound potions with simple or compound potions to try and make complex potions.  Though complex potions are the strongest you can make, the process is dangerous.  Mixing the wrong potions can cause violent reactions and set off dangerous explosions.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Alchemy Basics") + '\r\n'
'700\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I know only one formula for a complex potion– the combination of a compound potion with either a simple or compound potion.  Mix a potion of resistance with a potion of cure poison, then take that potion and mix it with a potion of protection, and you end up with a potion of divine cure.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Advanced Alchemy") + '\r\n'
'701\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Thief and Mercenary Guilds are the places you go to learn all kinds of skills.  Different guilds teach different skills, so if one doesn't have what you're looking for, try the guilds in a different town.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Thief and Mercenary Guilds") + '\r\n'
'702\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Quests aren't anything magical, they're simply opportunities...  Opportunities to learn a great deal or to make a great deal of money.  Try not to pass up the chances you get.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Quests") + '\r\n'
'703\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Try to equip everyone in your group with a bow, crossbow, or some other ranged weapon.  You can do a lot of damage to an opponent as they approach you, and ranged weapons let you attack flying creatures that otherwise couldn't be hurt.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Bows") + '\r\n'
'704\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Most warriors like to train in a variety of weapons.  Usually, one weapon is trained higher than the others, but few are ignored.  This provides great flexibility in combat, because you can use the weapon that is most effective against the enemy you face.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Generalization") + '\r\n'
'705\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Some monsters are resistant to nearly all magic spells.  If you run into one of these monsters, don't despair– use your magic to heal your warriors and strengthen their blows.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magic resistance") + '\r\n'
'706\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Albert Newton is a brilliant magical researcher, but his research always seems to take a long time to complete.  He certainly knows quite a bit about sorcerers and their magics, however.  If you have any questions about that, he's the person to talk to.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Albert Newton") + '\r\n'
'707\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I've heard tales of a powerful magical staff that boosts your magical reserves and can strike as swiftly as the wind itself. ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magical Staves") + '\r\n'
'708\t' + _x("npc conversation", "General stores will buy  nearly anything, but give terrible prices.  If a general store is the only store around and you need to sell something fast, go ahead and use it.  But if it can wait, you'll do better selling something to a more specific store.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "General Stores") + '\r\n'
'709\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Not all shops are the same!  Some stores offer lowly goods, while shops in other towns have excellent wares for sale.  You'll need to look around and find the good shops for yourself, but keep in mind:  You get what you pay for.  Great equipment never comes cheap.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Stores") + '\r\n'
'710\t' + _x("npc conversation", "This foul place is the center of the most serious crimes against nature the Necromancer's Guild has been committing.  My firm scout's advice is to avoid, avoid, avoid!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Castle Darkmoor") + '\r\n'
'711\t' + _x("npc conversation", "City councils are always looking for people to take care of local jobs for them.  If you need a little extra cash, try dropping by and asking about work.  There's a good chance they'll have something for you.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "City Councils") + '\r\n'
'712\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Your reputation affects how people deal with you.  Most people aren't going to trust you or confide in you if your reputation isn't good.  You'll only find friends from thieves and the like, and do you really want them as friends?  You'll need to help others and follow the laws to bolster your reputation.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Reputation") + '\r\n'
'713\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Try to stay close to chimney sweeps– they're good luck!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Chimney Sweeps") + '\r\n'
'714\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Apparently there's a new Thieves' Guild called the Shadow Guild that's competing with the established guilds across the lands.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Thieves' Guild") + '\r\n'
'715\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I just bought the deed to a bridge spanning the White Forest River.  It's a toll bridge!  Soon I'll be rich as my professional bridge managers make money from the tolls they charge and put it in my bank account!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Bridge Deed") + '\r\n'
'716\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I can never get work in Castle Ironfist.  I don't understand why.  It's almost as though they don't want people crawling around the castle.  Are they hiding something?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Castle Ironfist ") + '\r\n'
'717\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I travel with all kinds of people, carrying heavy loads from one place to the other.  I tell you though, unless you're powerful, your load will be lightened for you by all the bandits on the roads.  Stay off the roads between cities if you know what's good for you.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Roads") + '\r\n'
'718\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Many inns are scattered across Enroth, and I believe there are even a few that eke out a meager existence in the western reaches.  These provide the easiest way to get food and the safest rest.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Inns") + '\r\n'
'719\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Ever notice how the cost of Resurrection at a temple is exactly equal to all the gold you had with you when you died?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Resurrection Bills") + '\r\n'
'720\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If you find a great piece of equipment for a low price, by all means buy it.  You'll be able to sell it later for a profit, and maybe even get some use out of it until then.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Investing") + '\r\n'
'721\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I've cooked a lot of fish in my day, but never have I cooked one of the deadly eels that infest the waters north of Silver Cove.  I'd love a chance to do it, but not many people tangle with the eels and live.  But, oh, for a taste!  They say the eels are the best delicacy the world has to offer!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fish") + '\r\n'
'722\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Never run out of food!  You don't gain any benefit from rest when you have no food, and it's very easy to starve to death in the wilderness if you have no food.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Food Supply") + '\r\n'
'723\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Somewhere out there is a set of horseshoes that protect your horses' hooves perfectly, and never lets them get tired!  The places you could go if you had horses with those qualities!  Oh, well.  It's just a legend, most likely.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Horseshoes") + '\r\n'
'724\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Soon after Archibald's defeat, I was able to peek into the Royal Library after one of my many performances at Castle Ironfist.  Inside, I saw a statue of Archibald in magnificent detail.  He must have had the statue made when he thought he was going to win his insurrection, and Roland's kept it as some sort of memento.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Archibald Statue") + '\r\n'
'725\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Every spell caster knows, or should know, that certain spells and magical effects occur around dawn and dusk.  For instance, no Divine Intervention is possible at any other time.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dawn and Dusk") + '\r\n'
'726\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It is said that one of the islands east of Free Haven hides the buried treasure of Silveka the pirate.  Now, I know these stories are a dime dozen, but I swear this one is true!  If only the map could be found…") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Buried Treasure") + '\r\n'
'727\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The old Dragon Towers were built to protect the towns from flying creatures, but they'll shoot down anything within their range that's flying.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dragon Towers") + '\r\n'
'728\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Though the Church of the Moon celebrated the darker side of human nature, it is not to say that good could not come of their evil, just as evil came of the Church of the Sun's good.  During their heyday, the Church managed to create artifacts of great power– the Doomsday Cloaks.  If you ever find one, don't throw it away!  They're all very powerful and valuable.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Church of the Moon") + '\r\n'
'729\t' + _x("npc conversation", "A great spell when running errands, Lloyd's Beacon allows you to set up beacons that you can teleport back to.  Though the beacons don't last forever, with proper planning they last long enough to get the job done.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Lloyd's Beacon") + '\r\n'
'730\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Making a healing potion is a simple matter, if you have ingredients.  All you need are widoweeps berries and a flask with water.  Just mix the berries with the water, and…Voila!  Instant healing potion!  If you don't have any water handy, you can just eat the berries directly, but the effect isn't as strong.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Healing Potions") + '\r\n'
'731\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Sweet Water was an excellent venue for my music before the Night of Shooting Stars.  Now the road to that town is infested with devils, and they say the town is no more.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Ruin of Sweet Water") + '\r\n'
'732\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Isle of the Hermit, named by Lord Terrance for its remoteness, is difficult to travel to because of the turbulent waters south of Enroth.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Isle of the Hermit") + '\r\n'
'733\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Lots of people would like to invade Regna and take her spices, her metal, and her treasures.  The only thing that's kept Regna free all these years is her attention to metal smithing science and her arms sales to all the countries of the world.  Everyone criticizes Regna for that, but everyone buys Regnan weapons.  Talkin' outta both sides of their mouth, that's what those hypocrites do!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Regnan smithies") + '\r\n'
'734\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I wish I could have been part of Roland's expedition!  There's true bravery– how glorious that troop must have looked, armor and weapons gleaming in the sun.  Better to die valiantly in the battlefield with your lord, then to expire in the night, cold and alone.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Roland's Expedition") + '\r\n'
'735\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Astrology is often sneered at, but I tell you it's very real and important.  The most significant astrological event recently was that shooting star that fell from the sky out of Sagittarius.  It portends upheaval, disaster, and opportunity for the entire world.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Astrology") + '\r\n'
'736\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Merchants in the northeast aren't above hiring people to make sure that their competition isn't too competitive.  We try to avoid those areas and not get involved with any of the local petty struggles.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Organized Crime") + '\r\n'
'737\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Listen to the way a person greets you to get an idea how to deal with them, should they prove uncooperative.  You'll find that many people that share similar interests and professions will have the same attitude toward your choice of begging, bribing, or threatening them.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Listening") + '\r\n'
'738\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Don't tell anyone I told you this, but Roland isn't dead.  He simply needed a vacation from all of the pressures of being king, and he's hiding away on Abdul's Resort Isle under a false name.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Roland") + '\r\n'
'739\t' + _x("npc conversation", "To keep people like me away from their things, people will often trap their chests. ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Disarm Traps") + '\r\n'
'740\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Weather sure has been strange lately.  Why, last June it snowed!  Snow in June, who'd ever have guessed?  It is an ill omen, snow in summertime.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Weather") + '\r\n'
'741\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Despite all of my problems, at least the Temple of Baa cares about me and helps me out.  Not like the government we have now.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Temple of Baa") + '\r\n'
'742\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Boots are the cobbler's domain, and I don't know much about them, but I will say that you shouldn't overlook their usefulness.  They can go a long way to adding to your overall personal protection in battle.  Everyone should wear boots.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Boots") + '\r\n'
'743\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I imagine much of my work in the near future will be digging the graves of the people killed by the devils.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Graves") + '\r\n'
'744\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I can't even begin to tell you how awful produce prices have been in the market, recently.  I think someone's artificially fixing the prices low!  If this goes on much longer I'll be ruined!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Produce Prices") + '\r\n'
'745\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Be careful drinking liquids left in barrels; you never know how long it's been sitting there.  You could get sick doing something like that.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Liquids") + '\r\n'
'746\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The wheel spins in the most fascinating ways.  Sometimes I think that if everyone would take a little time out and watch the wheel spin, they would calm down, and be less likely to fight with one another.  But no one will listen to me.  I'm just a lowly potter.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Spinning Patterns") + '\r\n'
'747\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It's one thing to make the clothes, but the beauty usually comes from dying the clothes in interesting colors.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dyes") + '\r\n'
'748\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The fact that our king is missing is awful, but it must be the will of the gods.  How could anything happen that isn't the will of the gods?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Will of the Gods") + '\r\n'
'749\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Lord Temper won't even allow me to become a knight.  He said I wasn't smart enough to follow directions.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Osric Temper") + '\r\n'
'750\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Mice and rats are a relentless plague upon mankind!  I hear that a keep near New Sorpigal has the biggest rats in the world living in it.  <shuddering>  May I never see such horrors as long as I live!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Mice") + '\r\n'
'751\t' + _x("npc conversation", "With all of Blackwoode now destroyed, wood is going to be very scarce in Enroth.  We might see another Timber War starting soon.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Blackwoode") + '\r\n'
'752\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Tomb of Ethric the Mad is a wonder of fine stone cutting.  My grandfather helped build it.  He says there are some very cleverly concealed secret doors in the Tomb.  Why Ethric would care if a door was secret or not is beyond me, but hey– he was both rich and mad.  I guess he could do what he liked.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Ethric's Tomb") + '\r\n'
'753\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Why is it goblins have no luck raising chickens?\n\nThey plant the eggs too deep!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Joke of the Day") + '\r\n'
'754\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The one thing you can say's been good these days is the cold weather.  All the animals have really thick, valuable fur.  Only trouble is finding them.  Monsters been eating most of the good fur animals, I think.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fur") + '\r\n'
'755\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Just between you and me, I saw a werewolf when I was a werewolf in Blackshire!  I believe all the rumors about their curse.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Blackshire") + '\r\n'
'756\t' + _x("npc conversation", "When cattle rustling gets too hard, I usually spend my time hunting on some Lord's land.  Since most people are afraid to hunt there, those forests haven't been over-hunted.  Recently, though, the animals have been getting scarce.  Could have something to do with the western blight.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Poaching") + '\r\n'
'757\t' + _x("npc conversation", "In some places it is difficult to hunt for game.  You need to pack more food when you travel in swamps or deserts or snow, for example.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Game") + '\r\n'
'758\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Wilbur Humphrey has hired me several times to take notes on disaster reports filtering in from around the kingdom.  I think there's been a sharp increase in calamities since the disappearance of the king.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Records") + '\r\n'
'759\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The prince is far too young to manage a kingdom.  Wilbur Humphrey should be ruling the kingdom for himself, not in the name of a child.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Nicolai") + '\r\n'
'760\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If you ever find yourself in need of work, just stop by the city council's office in one of the large towns.  There's usually a job that needs doing.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "City Councils") + '\r\n'
'761\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The rumors of the dynasty collapsing and all the disasters have brought out the worst in humanity.  I need to be even more vigilant than normal to keep the peace.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Unrest") + '\r\n'
'762\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Take it from me, if you want a lucky charm, hang around a chimney sweep.  Sure, their banter can be annoying, but they're the luckiest people I know.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Chimney Sweeper") + '\r\n'
'763\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I have heard rumors that the recent 'winter during summer' spectacles have been caused by mischievous sorcerers who have learned to meddle with the weather.  I think it's part of a plot to create mass hysteria and open rebellion against the King.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Sabotage of Summer") + '\r\n'
'764\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The devils people are talking about causing havoc in the west are just misunderstood.  Baa says that they are our friends.  You just have to be respectful and run from them if you see them coming.  They need a lot of personal space, and get angry if they don't get it.  But that's only because they are superior beings.  If we were superior, all this would be easier to understand.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Devils") + '\r\n'
'765\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I'd love to sail the oceans on a big ship.  I could travel to all the islands and just be free of school and chores and my parents.  That would be wonderful!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Boats") + '\r\n'
'766 St\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Word is that the goblins are looking to buy weapons for raids on human towns.  I hear the regent has a sizeable bounty on the heads of any who deliver weapons to those evil little toads.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Arms Smugglers") + '\r\n'
'767\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Most any dragon that has a lair is absolutely loaded with gold.  They get it from all the paladins who try to kill them to make a name for themselves.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dragons' Gold") + '\r\n'
'768\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Some of the magic items you find around the world are cursed.  Almost none are pure curses, but many have side effects you won't like much.  You should carefully weigh the side effects against the benefits an item offers before using it.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Cursed items") + '\r\n'
'769\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Of course you know that spells cast at high noon draw their power directly from the sun.  It is in this way that the mightiest of magicians can afford the power it takes to enchant the magical items you find throughout the land of Enroth.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "High Noon") + '\r\n'
'770\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The desert is a land that should be avoided by all but the mightiest sorcerers and knights.  Filled with giants and dragons, nearly all who visit do not return.  Rumor has it that a strange pyramid in the desert holds untold riches and secrets waiting to be unearthed by some brave souls.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Desert") + '\r\n'
'771\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The pass leading to White Cap and Caste Stromgard has recently been taken by a group of ogres and greedy humans working together.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Icewind Pass") + '\r\n'
'772\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I've heard stories of a horrible curse that has possessed the town. Every time I've visited, however, everything seems normal.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Blackshire") + '\r\n'
'773\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Although no shipping companies are currently offering the service, Erathia, homeland of Queen Catherine Ironfist, can be reached in a voyage of three weeks or so, depending on the season.  Ain't never been there, but they tell me it's nice.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Erathia") + '\r\n'
'774\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Water walking is nice and all, but it doesn't beat a good ship and a good crew.  Not only are you slower than a ship, you have to worry about the spell wearing off, and you have to worry about sea serpent attacks.  Boats are the best way to travel by water.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Water Walking ") + '\r\n'
'775\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Resting only really works well in a comfortable place like an inn.  There you can regain lost strength and magic, and heal from most of your wounds.  If you must rest in the wilderness, be sure to have enough food!  Hungry people gain no benefit from rest.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Resting") + '\r\n'
'776\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Though not as effective as other healing spells, Healing Touch is in the school of spirit, which makes it easier for paladins to learn.  Also, body spells don't work in certain areas, so you will need to use Healing Touch instead of spells like First Aid or Power Cure.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Healing Touch") + '\r\n'
'777\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Shared Life is an excellent way to keep weaker party members alive when your party is being assaulted with area affect spells.  This spell combined with Power Cure can keep everyone alive when you get in over your head.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Shared Life") + '\r\n'
'778\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Many teachers do not want to be flooded by students, so they have moved to remote locations.  You might have to look around quite a bit to find them.  Generally, expert teachers know where their master teachers are.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Teachers") + '\r\n'
'779\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fame, in many ways, is an accumulation of the experiences you have and how you've managed to share with others.  Quests and brave deeds against monsters can make you famous.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fame") + '\r\n'
'780\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Personally, my favorite weapon is the mace.  When you get good at it, you learn to strike at hard parts on your opponent so that it bounces off instead of sinking in.  Saves time.  Anyway, when someone gets hit with a mace, it can stun them so bad that they stop fighting back.  And that's a fine thing.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Glory of the Mace") + '\r\n'
'781\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Never underestimate the staff!  Most people associate the staff with a mage, but that's not always the case.  Although you cannot use a shield with a staff, as you become more skilled you'll find that staves are the best defensive weapon around.  Not only that, but they have enough weight to stun people that are hit with it.  It's one of the best all around weapons available.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Staves") + '\r\n'
'782\t' + _x("npc conversation", "All of the schools of magic have eleven spells, but only ten can be found in the guilds of darkness.  The missing eleventh spell is called something like Dark Holding or Dark Containment.  No one alive seems to have learned it, and the guilds are very anxious to find it.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Dark Containment") + '\r\n'
'783\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Summoned by mages to guard areas or items, elementals are beings composed of one of the four primary elemental forces:  air, earth, fire, or water.  Elementals can freely use magics of their element, so be wary if you should battle them.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Elementals") + '\r\n'
'784\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Archibald, Roland's brother, mastered many magical arts and accomplished himself as a powerful sorcerer before his demise.  No one seems to know where he is buried, though.  It's as though he disappeared after Roland's ascension to the throne.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Archibald") + '\r\n'
'785\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Skilled merchants run many of the stores in Enroth.  You must be careful when buying and selling to make sure you are not getting ripped off.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Prices") + '\r\n'
'786\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It's dangerous to carry a lot of money with you.  Banks provide a safe place to store large amounts of money.  Though they don't credit you with interest, you don't have to worry about pickpockets.  That's good enough for me.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Banks") + '\r\n'
'787\t' + _x("npc conversation", "In the center of Dragonsand you can find a pyramid marking the Tomb of the Ship, or so they say.  I've scoured the desert and found nothing but dragons and titans to run from.  That doesn't mean it's not there– I had to get out of that desert while the getting was good.  A very dangerous place!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Pyramid ") + '\r\n'
'788\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I do not like assassins, or men of low character.  And it seems that both types of criminal are spreading through the land like the plague these days.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Low Character") + '\r\n'
'789\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Some creatures you'll run into can be reasoned with if you have a fear spell available.  You can avoid unnecessary and wasteful injury by scaring off your enemies rather than simply fighting with them.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Monsters ") + '\r\n'
'790\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Sometimes bandits and highwaymen will accept you if they don't think you're 'upstanding citizens.'  The weak, however, are always robbed.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Highwaymen") + '\r\n'
'791\t' + _x("npc conversation", "You must be careful when opening some locks.  Many people don't consider a lock enough of a deterrent, so they will trap their doors or chests to try and frighten off or kill a would-be thief.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Traps") + '\r\n'
'792\t' + _x("npc conversation", "All of the really bad disasters started happening after the Night of the Shooting Stars two years ago.  Not much has gone right since then, except the Temple of Baa.  They really help people.  They also say that King Roland must have done something awful, 'cause the stars were avenging angels falling from Heaven to punish the wicked.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Shooting Stars") + '\r\n'
'793\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Let me tell you a secret.  There is no such thing as luck.  You make your own luck based on your outlook.  If you expect the worst to happen, it probably will, and you'll have a horrible time.  If, however, you look on the bright side and expect the best, you'll usually find it.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Luck") + '\r\n'
'794\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It's hard to travel through the snow.  Good thing you have people like me around!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Snow") + '\r\n'
'795\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Resting allows you to approach the new day with vigor and zest.  Resting will heal your wounds and recharge your magic.  Nothing finishes a hard day like a good camp, good dinner, and a good fire.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Benefit of Rest") + '\r\n'
'796\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Ever fantasize about discovering a huge horde of treasure?  I do.  They say there are three really big ones:  The first is the knowledge contained in the Royal Library.  The second is the treasure the obelisks lead to.  And the third is in Loretta Fleise's basement!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fortune") + '\r\n'
'797\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I'm not sure the towns to the west even exist anymore.  Merchants don't travel to there, and no one has come back from those areas yet.  I believe civilization ends at Blackshire, and even the people there are strange at times.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Western Areas") + '\r\n'
'798\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It may not seem like a big deal, but I like to supplement my cooking with fresh fruit.  You can find it most places just growing on trees, if you look.  Fruit trees have helped me out when I was hungry and had no money, and they could help you, too.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fruit Trees") + '\r\n'
'799\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I believe there is a spell that will allow you to create food for yourself out of thin air, but I can't imagine food made from magic tasting very good.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Create Food Spell") + '\r\n'
'800\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I don't suppose you've got any news of Sweet Water, do you?  No one I know has heard anything about the town for a year!  They're a long ways off from here…but a year?  Something must be wrong.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Sweet Water") + '\r\n'
'801\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I wonder about the council sometimes.  The decisions they've made and some of the laws they've stalled on have really contributed to the chaos around here.  They've stalled any official investigation of Roland's death, and I don't understand why.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Council Members") + '\r\n'
'802\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Practicing meditation may not seem like a big deal at first, but it can be a source of tremendous magical energy to the skilled.  Meditation masters can have many times the spell casting power as their less enlightened brethren.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Meditation") + '\r\n'
'803\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Although no shipping companies are currently offering the service, Erathia, homeland of Queen Catherine Ironfist, can be reached in a voyage of three weeks or so, depending on the season.  Ain't never been there, but they tell me it's nice.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Erathia") + '\r\n'
'804\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The next best thing to flying, if you fall off of a cliff or similar height; Feather Fall doesn't give you any control but it certainly keeps you alive.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Feather Fall") + '\r\n'
'805\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The legend of the Crossing is more than a thousand years old, but that doesn't stop people from repeating it from time to time.  The legend says that we all, and that even includes the elves, the dwarfs, and the goblins, came from the same place on a great ship that carried us across the void between the stars.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Crossing") + '\r\n'
'806\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I've heard portals exist that allow transit between two fixed places in Enroth.  Knowledge of these would provide another excellent and fast way to move around the world.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magic Portals") + '\r\n'
'807\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The gods oversee our lives and guide us constantly toward heaven and the light.  All you have to do is listen with your heart and do what it tells you to be admitted to heaven.  Have faith.  The gods will help you get there, if you'll listen to them.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Gods") + '\r\n'
'808\t' + _x("npc conversation", "They say the king was last seen fleeing toward Castle Kriegspire with an army of devils following him.  He never returned.  I think we may have to face up to the possibility that our good king was killed by those monsters.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fall of Roland") + '\r\n'
'809\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Teleportation is the way to go to minimize travel times.  Of course, you can move around pretty quickly by boat or by horse if you have a skilled person leading the way.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Travel Times") + '\r\n'
'810\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I came to Enroth during the time Regnans were invited by King Archibald to bring over a load of weapons to help in his fight against Roland.  When Archibald lost the war, Roland seized all the arms ships and forbade travel to Regna.  I've been stuck here ever since.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Arms Shipments") + '\r\n'
'811\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The simplest piece of a knight's equipment, the shield provides excellent defense for low hindrance and weight.  No warrior should be without a good shield in a fight.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Shields") + '\r\n'
'812\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Witches' Assembly of 638 was the greatest gathering of sorcerers and alchemists ever.  Since then, the popularity of the magical arts has declined, and persecution of groups like ours…er, theirs– has grown quite a bit.  It really is quite awful.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Witches") + '\r\n'
'813\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Merchants are businessmen first and foremost.  They will always try to buy low and sell high.  Don't be too upset with them; they need to make a living, too.  The way to get the best prices, both when buying and selling, is to try different markets.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Merchants") + '\r\n'
'814\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If you've determined that begging and bribing are of no use, and you simply must speak with a person, then the thinly veiled threat must be issued.  But remember to use this option sparingly, since only the best diplomats can stop the damage you'll do to your reputation if threats become your habit.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Threats") + '\r\n'
'815\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Nicolai has commissioned a bridge to be built from New Sorpigal to Mist.  I'm working for him by offering affluent members of society a chance at charter membership of the Nicolai Ironfist Bridge Fellowship.  The basic membership gets your name on a flagstone of the bridge and costs 50,000 gold– a small price to pay for immortality.  Are you interested?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Bridge") + '\r\n'
'816\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fetzil, the Prince of Thieves lieutenant, is smart; he knows enough to hide out when things get hot.  He's not an easy person to catch.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fetzil ") + '\r\n'
'817\t' + _x("npc conversation", "All of the really bad disasters started happening after the Night of the Shooting Stars two years ago.  Not much has gone right since then, except the Temple of Baa.  They really help people.  They also say that King Roland must have done something awful, 'cause the stars were avenging angels falling from Heaven to punish the wicked.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Shooting Stars") + '\r\n'
'818\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I hate taxes!  Why should we pay taxes anyway?  It's bad enough I have to spend my life working for other people; I need to pay them for the 'honor'?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Taxes") + '\r\n'
'819\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Cotton is found in Karigor, the island home of the Church of the Sun and the Church of the Moon.  It doesn't grow well anywhere else, and it's difficult to pick and seed, but it makes for wonderful soft clothes, if you can afford it.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Cotton") + '\r\n'
'820\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If I could actually use a weapon, I'd probably be better off joining a bandit group.  I bet they lead an easy life.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Brigands") + '\r\n'
'821\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Sure's been hard to get help recently.  What is a good farmer to do if he can't find strong workers during harvest times?  Go into bankruptcy and ruin, that's what!  Oh, woe is me!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Farm Help") + '\r\n'
'822\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I'd love to hear what the Oracle would say about the devils, the Temple of Baa, and Prince Nicolai.  Why won't the council consult the Oracle?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Oracle") + '\r\n'
'823\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Change is in the air and on the wind.  You can smell it and feel it.  Something big's going to happen soon.  I can always tell.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Change") + '\r\n'
'824\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Warm clothes won't help you resist the chill of Castle Darkmoor.  The undead there steal the warmth from your body with their touch.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Darkmoor") + '\r\n'
'825\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The blight that's afflicting western crops and animals is slowly spreading east.  Cows are affected first, and this is causing a very serious leather shortage.  You can expect the price of boots and belts and other leather goods to be increasing!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The Blight") + '\r\n'
'826\t' + _x("npc conversation", "This isn't the best job in the world, but at least the work is steady.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Labor") + '\r\n'
'827\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Taxes have been good under this King.  Archibald was terrible, much worse than his father.  I thought I would be ruined by Archibald's cruel taxes.  May he nor his like never hold the throne again!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Taxes") + '\r\n'
'828\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Let me tell you, some bookshelves or desks or other furniture can be crafted to conceal a secret passage.  You can walk through a room and never realize there were two or three other hidden exits.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Secret Passages") + '\r\n'
'829\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If you ever take a trip near Star Lake, be sure to check out the beautiful statues on the island in the center of the lake.  They are so life-like they're breathtaking!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Statues at Star Lake") + '\r\n'
'830\t' + _x("npc conversation", "What is big and red and eats rocks?\n\nA big red rock eater!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Joke of the Day") + '\r\n'
'831\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Come to think of it, the animals all started to go away when the stories of the devils in the West started cropping up.  Yep.  That's probably it.  Pesky critters!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Spooked Animals") + '\r\n'
'832\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I'm so pitiful, the bandits that prowl the roads even laugh at me!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Wretch") + '\r\n'
'833\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If you think your reputation is getting too bad for people to tolerate you, you should check yourself into a temple and start donating, my friend.  The temple will spread word of your generosity far and wide, and people will think better of you for it.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Notoriety") + '\r\n'
'834\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If you're going to hunt anything, you'll need a bow.  I don't think you are fast enough to chase a deer down with your sword.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Bows") + '\r\n'
'835\t' + _x("npc conversation", "When I was much younger, I had a chance to see the ruined library of the Church of the Moon at Karigor.  It was made entirely of jade and marble, and once contained the wisdom of the ages within its hallowed halls. If ever you have a chance to visit, take it!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Library at Karigor") + '\r\n'
'836\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The main Temple of Baa is just northwest of Blackshire.  Only members of Baa are allowed inside.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Temple") + '\r\n'
'837\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The High Council isn't just an ordinary city council– they are the body that represents the lords of the land.  They vote on important matters of state that need to be taken before the king.  They also control access to the Oracle.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "High Council") + '\r\n'
'838\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It is important for guards to be patient.  We can't go out and look for trouble; we need to wait for trouble to find us.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Patience") + '\r\n'
'839\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The poor queen has lost both her father and her husband.  Hopefully, nothing will happen to Nicolai. ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Catherine") + '\r\n'
'840\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I'm wondering if something foul indeed fell from the sky that Night two years ago.  I am not, however, of the opinion that it was an avenging angel!  More like a devil, if you ask me!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Meteors") + '\r\n'
'841\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I'm fine!  Why do you ask?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Madness") + '\r\n'
'842\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Why do grown-ups always have to fight?  Why can't people just get along?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Fighting") + '\r\n'
'843 Sn\t' + _x("npc conversation", "What're ya gallivanting' around here for on a Sunday?  It's a day of rest, kid, REST, I say!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Rest") + '\r\n'
'844\t' + _x("npc conversation", "There are two kinds of magic armor– armor that increases your protection, and armor that is lighter and easier to wear.  A few rare kinds of armor have both of those properties.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magic Armor") + '\r\n'
'845\t' + _x("npc conversation", "When a wand runs out of charges, you've lost the value of the wand.  They can never be recharged, but it's usually possible to find a sucker to buy the wand at full price  just before the charges run out.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Recharging Wands") + '\r\n'
'846\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Combining potions in the right proportions can achieve formulas that do very unusual things.  The Guild of Alchemists closely guards the secrets of which potions have which effects.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Potions") + '\r\n'
'847\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I don't have much taste for civilization, but you can rest assured that more goods and services will be available on the east coast of Enroth than anywhere else– particularly Free Haven.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Civilization") + '\r\n'
'848\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Horses provide an excellent means of travelling if you can afford the cost.  All of the towns and castles  on the mainland have stables where you can hire horses.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Horses") + '\r\n'
'849\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Mages are so lazy, they've formulated several spells to transport people instantly from place to place.  These spells are good, but there's nothing like a REAL journey.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magic Transportation") + '\r\n'
'850\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I've heard there are sorcerers for hire who can cast the Walk on Water spell if you can't do it yourself.  They charge a lot, though.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Water Walking Spells") + '\r\n'
'851\t' + _x("npc conversation", "You need to be careful when planning your boat travels.  Certain areas are too dangerous to sail to during parts of the year.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Travel Seasons") + '\r\n'
'852\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It is important to get treatment for diseases and poisons.  The longer they go untreated, the harder they are to cure.  Getting poisoned or diseased more than once worsens your situation.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Disease and Poison") + '\r\n'
'853\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The highest level spell in the school of body, Power Cure is an effective way to heal the entire party quickly.  One Power Cure heals more damage faster than 4 smaller healing spells.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Power Cure") + '\r\n'
'854\t' + _x("npc conversation", "You generally have more hit points than spell points, so it is often faster to heal yourself as best as possible with magic, then rest.  You can cut down on your resting times quite a bit this way.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Resting") + '\r\n'
'855\t' + _x("npc conversation", "As your level of experience increases, so does the amount of experience you need to improve.  You'll get more benefit from a magical effect or reward that increases your level directly later in your life because of this rule.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Experience") + '\r\n'
'856\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Prince Nicolai shows incredible perception and creativity for his young age, much like his father did.  I don't think people give him enough credit– they're more concerned with his age than his ability.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Nicolai") + '\r\n'
'857\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It pays to know how to use two or three different kinds of weapons, kid.  That way you can change tactics in battle if an opponent isn't getting hurt by your favorite fish gutter, if ya know what I mean!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Weapons") + '\r\n'
'858\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Osric is not only a master warrior, but an ingenious general.  I'm glad to see that he's not taking the recent attacks by the devils lightly.  He's already working on ways to fight back, but the situation looks pretty grim.  If anyone can come up with a way to fight them, however, it's Osric.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Osric Temper") + '\r\n'
'859\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If you're facing an opponent that can't be put down with direct damage spells, try a mental attack spell, or something that freezes them in place.  This can often give the warriors in your group time to pound the enemy into the ground while distracted by your spell.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Mental Attacks") + '\r\n'
'860\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Gharik attempted to recreate some of the weapons from the Time of Wonders in his forge.  He was never successful, but a number of his experiments provided useful information for enchanting weapons and summoning creatures.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Gharik") + '\r\n'
'861\t' + _x("npc conversation", "A few Guilds of the Elements exist.  Though their knowledge of the individual elements isn't as pervasive as the more specialized guilds, they are an excellent resource to broaden your knowledge of all the elements.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Elemental Magic Guilds") + '\r\n'
'862\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The essence of life!  Gold oils the squeaking wheel, silences the witness, or loosens his tongue.  Gold puts food on the table and wood in the fire.  How I love thee, O mighty gold.  Never run out of gold, my friend.  Never!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Gold") + '\r\n'
'863\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The most important part of being a merchant can't be taught.  You need to learn to notice a good buy when you see one, and make the good deals when you can.  If you pick up something for cheap in one town, there's a good chance you can sell it somewhere else for a profit.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Speculation") + '\r\n'
'864\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I traveled to the lands west of Blackshire recently, and what I saw chilled my blood.  Devils running about a ruined, blighted landscape, killing any humans they ran across.  Something is terribly wrong.  I just don't know why someone isn't doing something about it!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Devils") + '\r\n'
'865\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Compared to many countries, Enroth is a very tolerant kingdom.  Nonetheless, you can end up in jail if you commit enough crimes and are foolish enough to show your face to a guard.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Law and Jail") + '\r\n'
'866\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Diplomacy is the key to negotiation, and negotiation is the key to many closed doors in the world.  You must be able to sip champagne with the highest lords and guzzle ale with the lowest scum if you want to succeed.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Negotiating") + '\r\n'
'867\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Find a penny, pick it up, all the day you'll have good luck!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Find a Penny") + '\r\n'
'868\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Most of the great treasure you'll find will be locked away in a chest or box.  It only makes sense to protect your valuables.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Chests") + '\r\n'
'869\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It is better to talk and let them think you a fool than to keep silent and prove it!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Talking") + '\r\n'
'870\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Poor Eric's temper matches the weather in his kingdom.  Seeing a smile on his face is about as rare as seeing the sun in White Cap.  He's got the wrong way of looking at things, ol' Eric does.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Eric Von Stromgard") + '\r\n'
'871\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Lady Fleise is the most difficult mistress to work for in all Enroth, you can be sure of that!  Penny pinching, heart of stone she has!  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Loretta Fleise") + '\r\n'
'872\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Different terrains are easier to forage and hunt in.  You don't need to use quite as much food in grasslands, for example, as you do in the desert.  Keep this in mind when you choose a place to camp.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Food Supply") + '\r\n'
'873\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Times are tough, and the banks have stopped giving interest payments on deposits recently.  Don't expect anything but security when you put your money in the bank– interest is a thing of the past!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Time") + '\r\n'
'874\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Loretta's managed to make money by creating and exploiting her lead position in the shipping industry.  She's able to manipulate shipping prices all over the kingdom which brings in quite a bit of money.  I only wish I handled her accounts.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Loretta Fleise") + '\r\n'
'875\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Better and fresher food that keeps longer is also more expensive.  People out west have figured out the trick of making food that keeps for a long time.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Cost of Food") + '\r\n'
'876\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Herbs can be used to create magical potions.  I don't know the procedure, but I know it's possible.  I wonder how those taste?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Alchemy") + '\r\n'
'877\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Although it can be expensive, travel using the stables is faster than most any other way, excepting magic, and not many people can do that!  If you're broke, you'll have to hoof it yourself, but don't forget the food cost of travelling by foot!  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Price of riding") + '\r\n'
'878\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I love to perform!  I love to travel!  There is no life like that of a bard.  The best gossip, the best food, and, most importantly, the best drink available… why would I ever want to be anything else?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Songs") + '\r\n'
'879\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Though you can't hear it, the stars and the planets sing as they travel through the sky.  It is the Music of the Spheres– the grandest symphony in the universe!") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Music of the Spheres") + '\r\n'
'880\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I've heard there are sorcerers for hire who can cast the Walk on Water spell if you can't do it yourself.  They charge a lot, though.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Water walking Spells") + '\r\n'
'881\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Flying is certainly easier than walking.  Safer, for the most part, too.  The only problem is that the Fly spell continually drains your power, so you need to plan your flight trips carefully so the spell doesn't run out.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Flying") + '\r\n'
'882\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Water walking– my specialty– permits you to walk across most bodies of water as though you were on dry land.  You have to be careful, though, or the spell will run out while you're still over the water.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Water walking Spells") + '\r\n'
'883\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I've had to rescue a number of doomed expeditions, and let me tell you the one thing I've learned.  If you go somewhere that you don't think you can handle, RETREAT.  No one will think less of you for it.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Retreat") + '\r\n'
'884\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The magics of mind, body, and spirit are the magics of the soul and the self.  To improve one's understanding of them is to improve one's standing with the gods.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Self Improvement") + '\r\n'
'885\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Many people have contempt for the simple music of a travelling minstrel, but it is the work of a lifetime to get good at what I do.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Music") + '\r\n'
'886\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Many areas with magical powers are scattered around the world.  Most often, they are in out of the way locations.  It's to your best benefit to try and discover and use as many of these as you can.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Special Locations") + '\r\n'
'887\t' + _x("npc conversation", "People say bad things about my homeland of Regna all the time, but they don't know what they're talking about.  Never will you find a more fun loving, happy people than on Regna, nor a more fiercely independent people.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Regna") + '\r\n'
'888\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The best way to learn is to make sure to fight challenging opponents.  You don't grow by picking on things weaker than yourself.  The true path to glory leads through winning tougher and tougher battles.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Opponents") + '\r\n'
'889\t' + _x("npc conversation", "There is a mystical deck of tarot cards some claim to have seen.  No person ever sees the deck twice.  To draw from the deck is to draw a new hand in the game of life.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Tarot Cards") + '\r\n'
'890\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Most of the dangerous areas left in the world are found to the west.  Paradise Valley and Dragonsand are the most notable, though the western parts of the Frozen Highlands and the Mire of the Damned are difficult as well.  As a general rule, the farther west, the more difficult.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "The West") + '\r\n'
'891\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I can't stress the importance of diplomacy enough.  A good diplomat can excuse any action, no matter how foul. ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Diplomacy") + '\r\n'
'892\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Devils!  Bah!  They're nothing more than illusions created by mages hiding vast treasure somewhere in Paradise Valley.  I know a few of those sorcerers personally, you see.  This ring I'm wearing was a gift from one of them.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Devils") + '\r\n'
'893\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Some people are born to trade, or negotiate, or fight, or study.  I'm born to steal, and I'm pretty good at it.  Times are a lot harder now because of all the calamities; it's hard to find things worth stealing anymore– people are way too careful with what they have.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Stealing") + '\r\n'
'894\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Thank God for Sundays!  If I had to work every day I think I would revolt against my noble oppressors and replace them with a capitalist-bourgeoisie run quasi-democratic society where I would still have to work long hours for little pay.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Labor") + '\r\n'
'895\t' + _x("npc conversation", "I wonder what life was like before the Silence with a governor in charge of everything?  It couldn't have been very good, or there wouldn't have been a rebellion.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Governor") + '\r\n'
'896\t' + _x("npc conversation", "There are three styles of hats popular these days, ranging from the cloth hat to the fancy, expensive sort made by the highest quality tailors.  Wizards like to enchant quality hats because they're lighter than helms and don't block your vision.  Also, a certain kind of conical hat seems easier to enchant than others.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Hats") + '\r\n'
'897\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Before the Silence was the Time of Wonders.  Magical creations handled all the hard labor– I wish I had one to do my chores.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Time of Wonders") + '\r\n'
'898\t' + _x("npc conversation", "All are equal before the majesty of the law:  Rich man as well as poor is prohibited from sleeping under bridges, stealing bread and begging for change.  –Voltaire") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Majesty of Law") + '\r\n'
'899\t' + _x("npc conversation", "It's easier to let a barrel roll down hill than to push it up.  Sometimes it's better to just go with the flow.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Advice") + '\r\n'
'900\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Not all clay is created equal.  The best clay can be found in the bed of the rivers and streams flowing past Free Haven.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Clay") + '\r\n'
'901\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Some articles of clothing have been enchanted.  It will benefit you to wear these types of magic clothes.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Magic Clothes") + '\r\n'
'902\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Everyone should wear shoes, not just nobles and rich people!  What are you going to do if you hurt your feet?  How are you going to keep working?") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Shoes") + '\r\n'
'903\t' + _x("npc conversation", "If I was smart, do ya think I'd be digging ditches for a living?  Be serious, please.") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Intelligence") + '\r\n'
'904\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Grindstones are so hard to make and find, it's a wonder anyone ever becomes a miller.  I hear that Karigor has a great rock quarry that turns things like millstones out by the hundreds.  ") + '\t' + _x("npc conversation", "Grindstones") + '\r\n'
